parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash, and the delay in repairing or replacing the defective airbag can put drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: None
as the issue is related to a potential failure in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to lock up or lose power, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel locks up or freezes
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the power steering warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to jerk or vibrate, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel jerks or vibrates while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the vehicle makes a grinding or clunking noise while steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Electronic Controls Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and electronic controls can cause the steering wheel to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel controls (e.g. cruise control
audio controls) malfunction
the steering wheel feels stuck or binding
the vehicle's electronic systems (e.g. lights
wipers) malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, stalling, and failure of various components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Unusual sounds from automatic door locks
feeling of drag or stall while driving
lack of power while driving
overheating of dashboard and driver foot area
burning smell
and failure of various components such as the alternator
key switch
and emission monitoring computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: HVAC system failures can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents due to reduced visibility.
symptoms: HVAC blower motor only works on high speed
grinding noises
AC switch failure
hot dial when turning off AC or heater
and failure of the AC clutch to disengage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent damage to wiring can cause electrical system failures, leading to a range of problems, including loss of power, stalling, and failure of various components, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine wiring damage
transmission malfunction
and engine coolant temperature sensor wire failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission failures can cause loss of power, stalling, and failure to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Feeling of drag or stall while driving
lack of power while driving
and failure to shift gears.
